## Improvement 5 — General UX Declutter

### 5a. Remove the pulsing animation from Multi-page badge

The amber badge with `animate-pulse` is distracting. Remove `animate-pulse` from the badge className in `EditorLayout.tsx` line 338. The dot alone is enough visual indicator.

```tsx
// Before
className="... animate-pulse shadow-[0_0_12px_rgba(245,158,11,0.1)]"

// After
className="... shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(245,158,11,0.06)]"
```

### 5b. Make the "Multi-page" badge non-alarming for 2-page resumes

Many professional CVs are 2 pages. The amber pulsing badge is too alarming. Change it to a softer neutral badge:

```tsx
{pageCount > 1 && (
  <div className="flex items-center gap-1.5 px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full bg-zinc-900/80 border border-zinc-700 text-[9px] font-semibold text-zinc-400 tracking-wide">
    <span className="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-zinc-500" />
    <span>{pageCount} Pages</span>
  </div>
)}
```

### 5c. Header visual cleanup

The header currently has: `Landing | Logo | product Manager | MULTI-PAGE badge | CLOUD SYNC badge | user avatar | ATS Audit | Settings`

That's 8 items which is cluttered. Suggested cleanup:

**In `src/layouts/EditorLayout.tsx` header section:**

1. Move `Settings` icon button **inside** the user avatar dropdown (not a separate button)
2. Or simply reduce the gap between items and use `gap-2` instead of `gap-3` for the right side

Actually, a smaller change: just remove the outer ring/border from the status badges so they look more like inline text than pill badges. This reduces visual weight significantly.

Change the badge border from `border border-*-500/35` → `border border-*-500/15` (reduce opacity from 35 to 15).

### 5d. SectionSidebar — compact the workspace nav

**File:** `src/components/SectionSidebar.tsx`

The left sidebar "WORKSPACE" section with Edit Resume, Preview, ATS Check links + the "RESUME COMPLETION" bar + "RESUME EDITOR" tips box takes a lot of vertical space.

Suggestion: Collapse the "RESUME EDITOR" tips box by default, showing only a small "?" icon that expands on click. This saves ~120px of sidebar space.

In `SectionSidebar.tsx`, find the "RESUME EDITOR" tips section and wrap it in a collapsible:

```tsx
